  "instructions": [
    "Pat dry the fish fillets with a paper towel.",
    "Season the fillets with salt and pepper.",
    "Heat olive oil in a nonstick skillet over medium heat.",
    "Sear the fish for 2-3 minutes on each side until cooked through and lightly browned.",
    "Let the fish rest for a minute, then slice into sashimi-thin pieces.",
    "Toss mixed greens, cucumber, and tomato in a large bowl.",
    "Add the sliced fish, mixed peel, capers, grated ginger, and optional soy sauce to the greens.",
    "Drizzle with fresh lemon juice and toss gently to combine.",
    "Sprinkle toasted sesame seeds over the salad.",
    "Season with additional salt and pepper to taste.",
    "Serve immediately for a crisp, light flavor."
  ],
